SIMPLE: animism
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Animism
<hw>An"i*mism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>animisme</ets>, fr. L. <ets>anima</ets> soul. See
<er>Animate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The doctrine, taught by Stahl,
that the soul is the proper principle of life and development in the
body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The belief that inanimate objects and the phenomena
of nature are endowed with personal life or a living soul; also, in an
extended sense, the belief in the existence of soul or spirit apart from
matter.</def> <rj><au>Tylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Animist</ent>⟦br⟧
